<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910531-0043</DOCNO><DOCID>910531-0043.</DOCID><HL>   Who's News:   InterVoice Appoints   David Brandenburg   To Second Top Post</HL><DATE>05/31/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B2</SO><CO>   INTV WNEWS</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>COMMUNICATIONS TECHNOLOGY (CMT)</IN><NS>PERSONNEL ANNOUNCEMENTS, PROMOTIONS, APPOINTMENTS (PER)</NS><RE>TEXAS (TX)</RE><LP>   DALLAS -- InterVoice Inc. said David Brandenburg, itschief operating officer, was named to the additional positionof president, succeeding Allen Fleener, who is retiringeffective tomorrow.   The appointment of Mr. Brandenburg, 46 years old, followsother top management changes at InterVoice, which makessystems that allow users to retrieve information via theirtelephones. The company named Daniel Hammond, a companyfounder and its chief executive officer, as chairman inDecember, succeeding another company founder. Mr.Brandenburg, a company director, was named to the new chiefoperating officer position and the company's executivecommittee just last July.</LP><TEXT>   The company said Mr. Fleener, who is 61 today, will act asa consultant to the company and will remain on the company'sboard at least until the annual meeting in July.   For the year ended Feb. 28, InterVoice had net income of$3.8 million, or 74 cents a share, a 45% decline from theprevious year. Sales for the year fell about 15% to $20.6million.</TEXT></DOC>